HEADWORD: Pedetentous
<hw>Ped`e*ten"tous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pes</ets>, <ets>pedis</ets>, foot + <ets>tendere</ets> to stretch
out: cf. L. <ets>tentim</ets> by degrees.]</ety> <def>Proceeding step by
step; advancing cautiously.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That <qex>pedetentous</qex> pace and <qex>pedetentous</qex> mind
in which it behooves the wise and virtuous improver to walk.</q>
<rj><qau>Sydney Smith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

